snippet.textDisplay: I appreciate that Christopher Nolan is willing to make an earnest film rather than a self-aware one. So many movies seem to want to avoid taking themselves too seriously, and ultimately feel like forgettable fluff as a result. Nolan risks being serious, and he makes me feel the tension of suspense that I used to feel from movies as a result.

snippet.textDisplay:
TENET is a palindrome.


As far as the trailer is concerned it's about a group of people or maybe operatives who are allowed to time travel to the crucial points in the future or past.


The only catch is, they will arrive in the near future of the desired event and the time will rollback till the time fed in the travel machine (or that mechanism) is reached.


E.g. If they decided to be at Bangalore Whitefield Road at 15:00 on the 21st of December 2019 to avoid the misfortunate event,


Then they will arrive at 15:02 or may be 15:03 and will start traveling backward in the chronological frames of those places. They will have only that 2-3 minutes of the time window to understand what happened there and how to avoid it by tweaking the event in real-time.


Interesting
